# How PostgreSQL Divides Rows

Suppose

```
10 Rows

↓

4 Groups
```

Calculation

```
10 ÷ 4

=

2

Remainder

=

2
```

Therefore

```
Group 1

↓

3 Rows

----------------

Group 2

↓

3 Rows

----------------

Group 3

↓

2 Rows

----------------

Group 4

↓

2 Rows
```

General Rule

Any extra rows are distributed

starting from

the first group.

