```

Expected Output

| Date | Sales | Next Day |
|------|------:|---------:|
|1 Jan|100|120|
|2 Jan|120|150|
|3 Jan|150|130|
|4 Jan|130|NULL|

This uses

```
LEAD()
```

---

# First Value Example

Suppose

employees

are sorted

by salary.

Business asks

```
Show

Every Employee

+

Highest Salary
```

Instead of

calculating

```
MAX()
```

we can simply

retrieve

the first row

using

```
FIRST_VALUE()
```

---

# Last Value Example

Business asks

```
