# Navigation vs Aggregate Functions

Aggregate Functions

```
Calculate

Mathematical Result
```

Examples

```
SUM

AVG

COUNT
```

---

Navigation Functions

```
Return

Another Row's Value
```

Examples

```
LAG

LEAD

FIRST_VALUE
```

This is the biggest conceptual difference.

---

# Navigation vs Ranking

Ranking

```
Assign

Position
```

Navigation

```
Return

Another Row
```

Completely different purposes.

---

# Navigation Functions Need ORDER BY

Unlike

some aggregate window functions,

navigation functions

almost always

require

```
ORDER BY
```

Reason

Without an ordering,

SQL cannot determine

what

"previous"

or

"next"

means.

---

# PARTITION BY with Navigation

Suppose

business asks

```
Previous Salary

Within Department
```

Query

```sql
LAG(salary)

OVER
(
PARTITION BY department

ORDER BY salary
)
```

Each department

becomes

its own timeline.

Navigation

never crosses

partition boundaries.

---

# Think Like a Data Engineer

Suppose

an IoT platform

collects

temperature readings.

Business asks

```
Current Temperature

↓

Previous Reading

↓

Difference
```

One query

using

```
LAG()
```

can detect

temperature spikes.

