↓

Previous Visit

↓

Days Between Visits
```

Navigation functions

support

clinical analytics.

---

# Logical Execution

Conceptually

```
Read Rows

↓

Partition

(Optional)

↓

Sort

↓

Locate Current Row

↓

Navigate

↓

Return

Referenced Value

↓

Next Row
```

Unlike aggregate functions,

navigation functions

do not calculate totals.

They simply retrieve

values

from other rows.

---

# Performance Notes

Navigation functions

generally require

sorting.

Performance depends on

- partition size,
- ordering,
- available memory,
- number of rows.

Proper indexes

may help

reduce sorting work,

but execution plans

should always be verified

using

```sql
EXPLAIN ANALYZE
```

---

# Best Practices

✅ Always specify a meaningful `ORDER BY`.

✅ Use `PARTITION BY` when navigation should restart for each business group.

✅ Choose the correct function based on whether you need the previous, next, first, last, or Nth row.

---

# Common Mistakes

❌ Forgetting `ORDER BY`.

❌ Assuming navigation crosses partition boundaries.

❌ Confusing navigation with aggregation.

❌ Using `LAST_VALUE()` without understanding the default window frame.

