# Section Summary

In this subsection, you learned:

- Sorting is typically the most expensive part of window-function execution.
- PostgreSQL executes window functions using the `WindowAgg` operator after rows have been partitioned and ordered.
- Multiple window functions with the same window definition can often share the same sorting work.
- Appropriate indexes may reduce sorting costs, but they do not eliminate sorting in every case.
- `EXPLAIN ANALYZE` and thoughtful query design are essential for optimizing production window-function queries.

