# Execution Order

Conceptually,

PostgreSQL processes

a query

like this

```
FROM

↓

WHERE

↓

GROUP BY

↓

HAVING

↓

Window Functions

↓

SELECT

↓

ORDER BY

↓

LIMIT
```

Remember

Window functions

are evaluated

after

filtering

and

aggregation,

which is why

they cannot

be referenced

directly

in

```
WHERE
```

