# Printable Cheat Sheet

| Requirement | Function |
|-------------|----------|
| Running Total | `SUM() OVER()` |
| Running Average | `AVG() OVER()` |
| Total Per Group | `SUM() OVER(PARTITION BY ...)` |
| Previous Row | `LAG()` |
| Next Row | `LEAD()` |
| First Row | `FIRST_VALUE()` |
| Last Row | `LAST_VALUE()`* |
| Nth Row | `NTH_VALUE()` |
| Unique Number | `ROW_NUMBER()` |
| Shared Rank (Gaps) | `RANK()` |
| Shared Rank (No Gaps) | `DENSE_RANK()` |
| Quartiles | `NTILE(4)` |
| Deciles | `NTILE(10)` |
| Latest Record | `ROW_NUMBER()` |
| Remove Duplicates | `ROW_NUMBER()` |

\* For `LAST_VALUE()`, remember that the default frame often returns the current row. Use an explicit frame such as `ROWS BETWEEN UNBOUNDED PRECEDING AND UNBOUNDED FOLLOWING` when you need the last row of the entire partition.

